Description:
Grupo Brisa is looking for a talented Data Scientist Intern with high potential to integrate the Data Office.




Being part of our team means working in a Group of innovative companies with a focus on sustainability and a vision of the future. It means working in a Group that cares about people and their development and well-being (we are proudly certified as Empresa Familiarmente Responsável), with a culture guided by the values of ethics, innovation, excellence and people.

We are an international Mobility Operator, recognized as a leading European Motorway Group. We provide advanced mobility solutions for operators and end customers. With billions of annual transactions and travelers using our systems internationally for 50 years, we have built innovative solutions with interesting lines of research. Brisa Group manages more than 20 companies and around 3,000 employees throughout the country and in the USA.




Role and Responsibilities




Take part in identifying and acquiring relevant datasets, performing data cleaning, and conducting basic preprocessing tasks;
Assist in the design and execution of data analysis and experiments to support the evaluation of business hypotheses across various sectors;
Support the implementation, fine-tuning, and deployment of Artificial Intelligence models under the supervision of senior team members;
Create simple reports and dashboards that contribute to simplifying data insights for diverse audiences through basic storytelling and visualization techniques;
Collaborate with data engineers and IT professionals to ensure data availability and quality, and support the integration of models into production data pipelines;
Work with cross-functional teams to gain an understanding of business requirements and organizational challenges.




Experience, Skills and Qualifications

Recently completed higher education in Data Science, Computer Science, Information Technology, Engineering, Management, Mathematics, Statistics, or equivalent;
Basic proficiency in programming languages such as Python and/or SQL;
Fundamental understanding of machine learning algorithms and statistical concepts;
Exposure to Data Modeling, Data Wrangling, Data Visualization;
Good communication and interpersonal skills with the ability to collaborate across teams and levels;
Strong attention to detail and commitment to producing accurate results;
Certifications in Data Science or related fields are a plus;
Experience with big data technologies (e.g., Spark, Databricks) is a plus;
Basic knowledge of additional programming languages is a plus (e.g., R, Java, Scala);
Familiarity with cloud-based data solutions is a plus (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP);
Basic understanding of CI/CD and MLOps/AIOps tools is a plus (e.g., Git, Azure DevOps, MLflow);
Familiarity with Collaboration tools is a plus (e.g., Jira, Confluence).




